libite
------------------------------------------
Libite is a lightweight library of frog DNA that can be used to fill the gaps
in any dinosaur project. It holds useful functions and macros developed by
both Finit and the OpenBSD project. Most notably the string functions:
strlcpy(3), strlcat(3) and the highly useful *BSD sys/queue.h and sys/tree.h
API's.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.6-1
  libite-devel-2.6.2-1bl1
  libite5-2.6.2-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/troglobit/libite

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/troglobit/libite/archive/refs/tags/v2.6.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libite-2.6.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libite-2.6.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libite-2.6.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libite-2.6.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libite5-2.6.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libite-devel-2.6.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libite)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libite.README
  /usr/share/doc/libite/API.md
  /usr/share/doc/libite/ChangeLog.md
  /usr/share/doc/libite/HACKING.md
  /usr/share/doc/libite/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libite/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/libite/TODO.md

(libite5)
  /usr/bin/cygite-5.dll

(libite-devel)
  /usr/include/libite/conio.h
  /usr/include/libite/lite.h
  /usr/include/libite/queue.h
  /usr/include/libite/strdupa.h
  /usr/include/libite/strlite.h
  /usr/include/libite/strndupa.h
  /usr/include/libite/strnlen.h
  /usr/include/libite/tree.h
  /usr/include/lite
  /usr/lib/libite.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libite.pc

